{
  "document_id": "ps-89",
  "title": "Psalms 89",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "I will sing of your steadfast love, O Lord, forever;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "I declare that your steadfast love is established forever;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "You said, “I have made a covenant with my chosen one;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "‘I will establish your descendants forever"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Let the heavens praise your wonders, O Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "For who in the skies can be compared to the Lord?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "a God feared in the council of the holy ones,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "O Lord God of hosts,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "You rule the raging of the sea;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "You crushed Rahab like a carcass;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "The heavens are yours; the earth also is yours;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "The north and the south—you created them;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "You have a mighty arm;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Righteousness and justice are the foundation of your throne;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Happy are the people who know the festal shout,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "they exult in your name all day long"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "For you are the glory of their strength;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "For our shield belongs to the Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "Then you spoke in a vision to your faithful one and said,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "I have found my servant David;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "my hand shall always remain with him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "The enemy shall not outwit him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "I will crush his foes before him"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "My faithfulness and steadfast love shall be with him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "I will set his hand on the sea"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "He shall cry to me, ‘You are my Father,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "I will make him the firstborn,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Forever I will keep my steadfast love for him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "I will establish his line forever"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "If his children forsake my law"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "if they violate my statutes"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "then I will punish their transgression with the rod"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "but I will not remove from him my steadfast love"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "I will not violate my covenant"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "Once and for all I have sworn by my holiness;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "His line shall continue forever,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "It shall be established forever like the moon,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-38",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 38,
      "text": "But now you have spurned and rejected him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-39",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 39,
      "text": "You have renounced the covenant with your servant;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-40",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 40,
      "text": "You have broken through all his walls;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-41",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 41,
      "text": "All who pass by plunder him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-42",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 42,
      "text": "You have exalted the right hand of his foes;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-43",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 43,
      "text": "Moreover, you have turned back the edge of his sword,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-44",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 44,
      "text": "You have removed the scepter from his hand"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-45",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 45,
      "text": "You have cut short the days of his youth;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-46",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 46,
      "text": "How long, O Lord? Will you hide yourself forever?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-47",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 47,
      "text": "Remember how short my time is—"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-48",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 48,
      "text": "Who can live and never see death?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-49",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 49,
      "text": "Lord, where is your steadfast love of old,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-50",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 50,
      "text": "Remember, O Lord, how your servant is taunted,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-51",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 51,
      "text": "with which your enemies taunt, O Lord,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-89-52",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 52,
      "text": "Blessed be the Lord forever."
    }
  ]
}